    "summary": "The user, a Type 1 diabetic experiencing symptoms of hypoglycemia (shakiness, sweating, confusion) following exercise, repeatedly asks for permission to take insulin despite being unable to check their blood glucose levels. The assistant identifies the potential for low blood sugar, refuses to recommend insulin without a reading, and ultimately directs the user to emergency services when the user expresses fear of ketoacidosis.",
